context: Political unification returned in the mid-16th century, due to the efforts of Taungoo, <a0_0>a former vassal state of Ava.<a0_0/> Taungoo's young, ambitious <a1_0>king Tabinshwehti<a1_0/> defeated the more powerful Hanthawaddy in the Toungoo–Hanthawaddy War (1534–41). However, the largest empire in the history of Southeast Asia unravelled soon after <a2_0>Bayinnaung<a2_0/>'s death in 1581, completely collapsing by <a3_0>1599<a3_0/>.
